      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "mt1",
      "content": []
    },
    {
      "type": "chapter",
      "marker": "c",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": [
        "Habakkuk’s First Complaint"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "p",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "1"
        },
        "This is the burden that Habakkuk the prophet received in a vision:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "2"
        },
        "How long, O LORD, must I call for help"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "but You do not hear,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "or cry out to You, “Violence!”"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "but You do not save?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "3"
        },
        "Why do You make me see iniquity?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "Why do You tolerate wrongdoing?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "Destruction and violence are before me."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "Strife is ongoing, and conflict abounds."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "4"
        },
        "Therefore the law is paralyzed,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and justice never goes forth."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "For the wicked hem in the righteous,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "so that justice is perverted."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": [
        "The LORD’s Answer"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "5"
        },
        "“Look at the nations and observe—"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "be utterly astounded!",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1:5 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "LXX "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "Look, you scoffers, wonder and perish!"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "For I am doing a work in your days"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "that you would never believe"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "even if someone told you.",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1:5 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Cited in ",
                {
                  "type": "ref",
                  "loc": "ACT 13:41",
                  "content": [
                    "Acts 13:41"
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "6"
        },
        "For behold, I am raising up the Chaldeans",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1:6 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "That is, the Babylonians"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        " —"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "that ruthless and impetuous nation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "which marches through the breadth of the earth"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "to seize dwellings not their own."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "7"
        },
        "They are dreaded and feared;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "from themselves they derive justice and sovereignty."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "8"
        },
        "Their horses are swifter than leopards,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "fiercer than wolves of the night."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "Their horsemen charge ahead,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and their cavalry comes from afar."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "They fly like a vulture,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "swooping down to devour."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "9"
        },
        "All of them come bent on violence;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "their hordes advance like the east wind;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "they gather prisoners like sand."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "10"
        },
        "They scoff at kings"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and make rulers an object of scorn."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "They laugh at every fortress"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and build up siege ramps to seize it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "11"
        },
        "Then they sweep by like the wind"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and pass through."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "They are guilty;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "their own strength is their god.”"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": [
        "Habakkuk’s Second Complaint"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "r",
      "content": [
        "(",
        {
          "type": "ref",
          "loc": "PSA 11:1-7",
          "content": [
            "Psalm 11:1–7"
          ]
        },
        ")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "12"
        },
        "Are You not from everlasting,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "O LORD, my God, my Holy One?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "We will not die."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "O LORD, You have appointed them"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "to execute judgment;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "O Rock, You have established them"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "for correction."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "13"
        },
        "Your eyes are too pure to look upon evil,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and You cannot tolerate wrongdoing."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "So why do You tolerate the faithless?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "Why are You silent"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "while the wicked swallow up"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "those more righteous than themselves?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "14"
        },
        "You have made men like the fish of the sea,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "like creeping things that have no ruler."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "15"
        },
        "The foe pulls all of them up",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1:15 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Literally "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "He pulls all of them up"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        " with a hook;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "he catches them in his dragnet,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "and gathers them in his fishing net;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "so he rejoices gladly."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "16"
        },
        "Therefore he sacrifices to his dragnet"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and burns incense to his fishing net,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "for by these things his portion is sumptuous"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and his food is rich."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "17"
        },
        "Will he, therefore, empty his net"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and continue to slay nations without mercy?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "chapter",
      "marker": "c",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": [
        "The LORD Answers Again"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "1"
        },
        "I will stand at my guard post"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and station myself on the ramparts."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "I will watch to see what He will say to me,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and how I should answer when corrected."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": []
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "p",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "2"
        },
        "Then the LORD answered me:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "“Write down this vision"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and clearly inscribe it on tablets,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "so that a herald may run with it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "3"
        },
        "For the vision awaits an appointed time;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "it testifies of the end and does not lie."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "Though it lingers, wait for it,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "since it will surely come and will not delay.",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "2:3 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Or "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "Though He lingers, wait for Him, since He will surely come and will not delay"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "; see also LXX; cited in ",
                {
                  "type": "ref",
                  "loc": "HEB 10:37",
                  "content": [
                    "Hebrews 10:37"
                  ]
                },
                "."
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "4"
        },
        "Look at the proud one; his soul is not upright",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "2:4 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "LXX "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "If he should draw back, My soul has no pleasure in him"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        " —"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "but the righteous will live by faith",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "2:4 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Or "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "faithfulness"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "; cited in ",
                {
                  "type": "ref",
                  "loc": "ROM 1:17",
                  "content": [
                    "Romans 1:17"
                  ]
                },
                ", Galatians 3:11, and Hebrews 10:38"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        " —"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "5"
        },
        "and wealth",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "2:5 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "DSS; MT "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "wine"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        " indeed betrays him."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "He is an arrogant man never at rest."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "He enlarges his appetite like Sheol,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and like Death, he is never satisfied."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "He gathers all the nations to himself"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and collects all the peoples as his own."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": [
        "Woe to the Chaldeans"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "6"
        },
        "Will not all of these take up a taunt against him,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "speaking with mockery and derision:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "‘Woe to him who amasses what is not his"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and makes himself rich with many loans!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "How long will this go on?’"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "7"
        },
        "Will not your creditors suddenly arise"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and those who disturb you awaken?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "Then you will become their prey."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "8"
        },
        "Because you have plundered many nations,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "the remnant of the people will plunder you—"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "because of your bloodshed against man"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and your violence against the land, the city,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and all their dwellers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "9"
        },
        "Woe to him who builds his house"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "by unjust gain,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "to place his nest on high"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and escape the hand of disaster!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "10"
        },
        "You have plotted shame for your house"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "by cutting off many peoples"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and forfeiting your life.",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "2:10 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Literally "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "sinning against your soul"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "11"
        },
        "For the stones will cry out from the wall,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and the rafters will echo it from the woodwork."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "12"
        },
        "Woe to him who builds a city with bloodshed"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and establishes a town by iniquity!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "13"
        },
        "Is it not indeed from the LORD of Hosts"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "that the labor of the people only feeds the fire,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and the nations weary themselves in vain?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "14"
        },
        "For the earth will be filled"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "with the knowledge of the glory of the LORD"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "as the waters cover the sea."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "15"
        },
        "Woe to him who gives drink to his neighbors,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "pouring it from the wineskin until they are drunk,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "in order to gaze at their nakedness!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "16"
        },
        "You will be filled with shame instead of glory."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "You too must drink"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and expose your uncircumcision!",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "2:16 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "DSS, LXX, and Syriac "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "and stagger"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "The cup in the LORD’s right hand"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "will come around to you,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and utter disgrace will cover your glory."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "17"
        },
        "For your violence against Lebanon will overwhelm you,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and the destruction of animals will terrify you,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "because of your bloodshed against men"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and your violence against the land, the city,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and all their dwellers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "18"
        },
        "What use is an idol,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "that a craftsman should carve it —"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "or an image,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "a teacher of lies?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "For its maker trusts in his own creation;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "he makes idols that cannot speak."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "19"
        },
        "Woe to him who says to wood, ‘Awake!’"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "or to silent stone, ‘Arise!’"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "Can it give guidance?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "Behold, it is overlaid with gold and silver,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "yet there is no breath in it at all.”"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "20"
        },
        "But the LORD is in His holy temple;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "let all the earth be silent before Him."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "chapter",
      "marker": "c",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": [
        "Habakkuk’s Prayer"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "p",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "1"
        },
        "This is a prayer of Habakkuk the prophet, according to Shigionoth:",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "3:1 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "Shigionoth "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "is probably a musical term indicating the setting for the prayer."
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "2"
        },
        "O LORD, I have heard the report of You;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "I stand in awe, O LORD, of Your deeds."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "Revive them in these years;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "make them known in these years."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "In Your wrath, remember mercy!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "3"
        },
        "God came from Teman,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and the Holy One from Mount Paran."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "qr",
      "content": [
        "Selah",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "3:3 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "Selah "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "or "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fqa",
              "content": [
                "Interlude "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "is probably a musical or literary term; also in verses 9 and 13."
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "His glory covered the heavens,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and His praise filled the earth."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "4"
        },
        "His radiance was like the sunlight;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "rays flashed from His hand,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "where His power is hidden."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "5"
        },
        "Plague went before Him,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and fever followed in His steps."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "6"
        },
        "He stood and measured the earth;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "He looked and startled the nations;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "the ancient mountains crumbled;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "the perpetual hills collapsed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "His ways are everlasting."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "7"
        },
        "I saw the tents of Cushan in distress;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "the curtains of Midian were trembling."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "8"
        },
        "Were You angry at the rivers, O LORD?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "Was Your wrath against the streams?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "Did You rage against the sea"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "when You rode on Your horses,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "on Your chariots of salvation?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "9"
        },
        "You brandished Your bow;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "You called for many arrows."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "qr",
      "content": [
        "Selah"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "You split the earth with rivers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "10"
        },
        "The mountains saw You and quaked;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "torrents of water swept by."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "The deep roared with its voice"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and lifted its hands on high."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "11"
        },
        "Sun and moon stood still"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "in their places"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "at the flash of Your flying arrows,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "at the brightness of Your shining spear."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "12"
        },
        "You marched across the earth with fury;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "You threshed the nations in wrath."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "13"
        },
        "You went forth for the salvation of Your people,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "to save Your anointed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "You crushed the head of the house of the wicked"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and stripped him from head to toe."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "qr",
      "content": [
        "Selah"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "14"
        },
        "With his own spear You pierced his head,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "when his warriors stormed out to scatter us,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "gloating as though ready"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "to secretly devour the weak."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "15"
        },
        "You trampled the sea with Your horses,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "churning the great waters."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "b"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "16"
        },
        "I heard and trembled within;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "my lips quivered at the sound."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "Decay entered my bones;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "I trembled where I stood."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "Yet I must wait patiently for the day of distress"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "to come upon the people who invade us."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "s1",
      "content": [
        "Habakkuk Rejoices"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        " ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "17"
        },
        "Though the fig tree does not bud"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and no fruit is on the vines,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "though the olive crop fails"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "and the fields produce no food,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "though the sheep are cut off from the fold"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
